=comment Package: Gtk4, C-Source: shortcuttrigger
use v6.d;

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#--[Class Description]----------------------------------------------------------
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

=begin pod
=TITLE Gnome::Gtk4::KeyvalTrigger
=head1 Description

A L<Gnome::Gtk4::ShortcutTrigger|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/ShortcutTrigger> that triggers when a specific keyval and modifiers are pressed.

=head2 Uml Diagram
=for image :src<asset_files/images/plantuml/KeyvalTrigger.png> :width<70%> :class<inline>

=begin comment

=head2 Example
# Example use of module Gnome::Gtk4::KeyvalTrigger

=end comment

=end pod

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#--[Class Initialization]-------------------------------------------------------
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

=begin pod
=head1 Class initialization

=head2 new

=head3 :native-object

Create an object using a native object from an object of the same type found elsewhere. See also B<Gnome::N::TopLevelSupportClass>.

  multi method new ( N-Object() :$native-object! )

=end pod

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
=begin pod
=head2 new-keyvaltrigger

Creates a L<Gnome::Gtk4::ShortcutTrigger|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/ShortcutTrigger> that will trigger whenever
the key with the given C<$keyval> and C<$modifiers> is pressed.

=begin code
method new-keyvaltrigger (
  UInt() $keyval, UInt $modifiers
  --> Gnome::Gtk4::KeyvalTrigger
)
=end code

=item $keyval; The keyval to trigger for.
=item $modifiers; the modifiers that need to be present.

=head2 Example

Example to initialize the object

=begin code
my Gnome::Gtk4::KeyvalTrigger $keyvaltrigger;
$keyvaltrigger .= new-keyvaltrigger( GDK_KEY_M, GDK_SHIFT_MASK);
=end code

=end pod

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#--[Methods]--------------------------------------------------------------------
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

=begin pod
=head1 Methods
=end pod

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
=begin pod
=head2 get-keyval

Gets the keyval that must be pressed to succeed triggering this object.

=begin code
method get-keyval ( --> UInt )
=end code

Return value; the keyval. Note that the key value can be changed. Tests show that uppercase letters are changed to lowercase.

=end pod

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
=begin pod
=head2 get-modifiers

Gets the modifiers that must be present to succeed triggering this object.

=begin code
method get-modifiers ( --> UInt )
=end code

Return value; the modifiers. 

=end pod

